What’s actually going on

There are three forces at play:

1. Selection pressure
    * Environments decide what survives.
    * In zero-sum games → dominance is punished early.
    * In positive-sum systems → dominance can compound.
2. Visibility vs survivability
    * Too visible too early = target
    * Too hidden too long = no influence
    * Optimal = timed visibility
3. Game type matters
    * Elimination games (Survivor) → threat management > raw ability
    * Accumulation games (business, skill-building) → ability compounds

